VWR Corp. said its VWR Scientific unit acquired most of Sargent Welch Scientific Co. 's laboratory and science-education distribution business for about $21 million. 

Sargent Welch is a unit of Artra Group Inc. VWR said the acquisition is in keeping with its previously reported plan to focus on its laboratory-supply distribution operations, which had sales of about $330 million in the year ended Feb. 28.
As reported, VWR plans to spin off to shareholders its graphics supplies and textile-related operations. 

VWR said the acquired Sargent Welch businesses have annual sales of about $50 million. 

